le through the reflection filter. I’m wondering if I should consider using `MethodHandles`, or perhaps I could opt for hardcoded offsets, though that seems risky for version compatibility. I can also look into `jdk.internal.misc.Unsafe` and the method `objectFieldOffset(Class, String)`, which could potentially work. It's a bit tricky, but I’ll keep exploring these possibilities!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_N5HpT9IgfzCC6KcM9VCXZhEW|fc_0143742bd8b7753c016a026066093c819f9b65934167d07fc1\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"javap sun.misc.Unsafe | grep -E \\\"objectFieldOffset|get.*Field\\\"\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 543, \"output\": 613, \"cacheRead\": 41984, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 43140, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1778540631959, \"responseId\": \"resp_0143742bd8b7753c016a0260592878819f9568f9f132fa8538\"}}\n3671:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Considering Java reflections**\\n\\nI’m thinking about JVM coverage and whether native code can catch unsupported operations. It seems dynamic class loading might not be the way to go. I wonder if I can use the public `Unsafe`, but it's probably not a good idea. I’m contemplating invoking the `Field` constructor with `sun.reflect.ReflectionFactory`, but that doesn't seem ideal either. Maybe I should test the feasibility of `Unsafe` locally in a scratch Java file. I'm also noticing that private fields might be hidden from `Class.getDeclaredFields` due to JDK filters.\\n\\n**Exploring field offset options**\\n\\nI'm facing a challenge with offsetting private fields since the Field object isn't accessible through the reflection filter. I’m wondering if I should consider using `MethodHandles`, or perhaps I could opt for hardcoded offsets, though that seems risky for version compatibility. I can also look into `jdk.internal.misc.Unsafe` and the method `objectFieldOffset(Class, String)`, which could potentially work. It's a bit tricky, but I’ll keep exploring these possibilities!\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0143742bd8b7753c016a02605a0a50819f9b2351c27a3130a8\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABqAmBmaPQGDGp2pIAIBhccELuXGm_-ScTHCDMXJ_ALjd-U6qFjDW8Z5R1yQjIsJ6msYZBP6mCKOnaqURQ4l-eOfOw_2t1jMj7VP8TA185xJf5KV4HNaFVt0wd-Sp8UjMoIFeH2ae-iTxanjfCNAgJ2_PFY5W6WsR769jcnSL4e4jBDlY4xwuWtVDLYrwOJRViUP21ksH1_ZvQK0Bv7qPDcPqRf4UkMR2yJ0Ym8VH95ivkIpro3zvDAdq_iixhbQuGWjfAz_DsYGhbrvvG3T5bOnNir3S3wDJsRmrsg7UVJ2pYJ9cHGHGhiPzeDeWRzZ0rnspYH51mnL2QIHrtdlnbVjtbevppFiBrJB54etGdvGdVDNmdIVKObXuLuMkoizI-5mdyB9SI12KtWerJHKQVZvZqogONcYr9db4342hGksuG8UQ-Ce1RfgUSvtS7roCi7dJLD1Ja90DXtwhzByIF17usHQm4eTA8EVr8miqgTH8RAm-jfqHVXuFQMgNsQFrQyBRPNweq5lH5qBNvvwO6QwtWvqJ7izFQCW19UAMN_yAZM6WkuOk4p84Sw1PazlEzIntQJGBjRl8aBApA7incnJ8dw2Uj83iknia4z54jTRKwYP6yje_N7xGeZ1-j_nWg30uE1ycfokv6vpTf2RQFdZKFMVy5VBC16N_akR1a6rnexBxpz9e6_3Luz_OGdjcN2pn5_UoMoBB1hP9kKhHbtEAXbf1c-I6D7UPVHD6kE97j0f0GeqywX9p8q48LWUM94VPhR1-34FCpWLybT_mcrdIBSb-GRKCmocpmtlqT-VZfyC749Rplpoe2HUd1CEkzyoyx4OMRg1PL0W1HovbEQR-xTawOWHUQJZjU5VpZzAihxNiFIhCTunYfc9Wgko_c4b8u7riOaN2CLjJ9hAm0Q5dKVhfaoMbghSs1wwGPQ5PA93bGec-C11AnsYnTd01xzcYJshXnqNXXGMuUO1dw2MYZef94fGKXHL_O9XrTFWiq91UNmAGdlhDebxSDn59mtSe6Jt_yTpQO-bp4N_rMr6r8-fBsrM7HcC6TRz_EASeLVbzLU5R9xc05n3QVJbyH0oI6z6I9_cHfobj1fpfOO3UutPyrW4b6QtcK7Zwd2skHcJRia_T5GHXeNYjqNvuXV6xeNwXXyMG28qe8p5tBBa16d8k1I0kmA7-mRnE4TPURlVnlsb2Zhjz8ypVan5doj1k1rDgRxZFEINRPOmjhI1pvHJfHw-JlqJf0ZU0WuClm-KD6AV8WxsJGoH6OnQIGRV73v3WH6xXvkhTPKHkEW_Gm8LHuNBlT3Ur2ncvgf-yTScaaUTQHUL3bNVa8ut3qatk0JN2CA2IeYD-jLElj6QW_zkoWKdLT32ZpRItpGxzvCGO3r8evf2ULA_40e0dmJJHEmi1ScLYgYFGiuXnVZA74kWxA60t4hgbo_OITMkgXdY6IocMFRvvBbgTQFaNttk2YG5VDj2tlMMNj9yvtOmir6OTY8t2ykEKtXd54wdG1BWLdrq6LZaSSnt3_3F06cQtjv-DqF5